rance of Barracks and accountability of Institute property    Tickets are not required for December Commencement Ceremony  The doors to Jackson Memorial Hall will open at 9 30 a m  Seating is on a first come  first served basis  Due to space constraints and security reasons  coolers  backpacks and baskets are not allowed at any commencement ceremony location  Strollers must be able to be folded and out of the aisles  All carry in items are subject to search at the door  Please anticipate heavy traffic so you and your family should plan accordingly  Please be seated by 10 45 a m  The Superintendent will host a light reception for all graduates and family and friends in Moody Hall immediately following the ceremony in Jackson Memorial Hall    VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 